agents.help_text: Your team is the face of your business, engaging and conversing with your users. You can see the full list of agents, add new agents, and edit agent details from this page.
agents.help_html:
An Agent is a member of your Customer Support/Engagement team. Agents will be able to view and reply to messages from your users. The list shows all Agents currently in your account. Hover over an Agent to see the option to edit details for that agent, or click on тАЬAdd AgentтАЭ to add a new Agent. Agents you add will receive an email with a confirmation link to activate their account, after which they can access and respond to messages.

Access to Freshchat features are based on an Agent's role -

Agent - Agents with this role can only access the Team Inbox and conversations.

Super User - Super Users have access to Campaigns and FAQs in addition to the Team Inbox, but cannot see or modify any common settings.

Admin - Admin will have access to all Freshchat features enabled for your account.

You can also organize Agents into Groups. You can create Groups {help_link}

header.description: Automate your daily chat workflows, save time for your Agents, and help them focus on tasks that matter, with Advanced Automations.

auto_responder.label: Auto Responder
auto_responder.title: Automatically send a response
auto_responder.send_first_response: Send a first response with your terms and conditions.
auto_responder.send_reply_on_assignment: Send a reply when the conversation gets assigned to an agent.
auto_responder.send_reply_on_resolve: Send a reply when the conversation is resolved.

chat_rescuer.label: Chat Rescuer
chat_rescuer.title: Rescue an unattended conversation
chat_rescuer.assign_to_different_agent: Assign the conversation to a different agent when the agent has not replied in more than 2 minutes.
chat_rescuer.unresponse_agent: Send a response when the assigned agent has not replied for more than 2 minutes.

overflow_handler.label: Overflow Handler
overflow_handler.title: Handle overflowing groups
overflow_handler.send_expected_wait_time: Automatically send an expected-wait-time message when the assigned group is running beyond capacity.
overflow_handler.send_reply_unassigned: Automatically assign to a new group (overflow group) if the assigned group is running beyond capacity.

auto_escalation.label: Auto Escalation
auto_escalation.title: Escalations for SLA violations
auto_escalation.assign_escalated_conversation: Escalate conversations that are unattended for more than x mins to a group where supervisors can monitor and take actions.
